{"key":"processedPost-11701296","value":{"id":11701296,"first":11676286,"last":11726856,"when":1261531218,"utime":"12/23/09 03:20 AM","content":"All bulk substrates including coir should be pasteurized.&nbsp; There's more to pasteurization than just killing mold spores.&nbsp; By 'cooking', we release more of what the mycelium needs.&nbsp; Performance is almost always better on pasteurized bulk substrates than on non-pasteurized.<br /><br />I've often said coir can be used with no heat treatment, but that's more in answer to someone with green mold on their tray.&nbsp; My point is that it's the spawn which was contaminated, not the coir.&nbsp; You'll find performance is better if you'll pasteurize the coir.<br />RR","title":"Re: PF TEK solely comprising of manure and gypsum"}}